Tis the season for STEW 🤤 🥔🌽🍅

Texas Cowboy Stew is the easiest, most filling stew you’ll make all winter long! Check out the recipe below 👇🏾👩🏾‍🍳

✨ Texas Cowboy Stew ✨

1/2 lb ground beef or Turkey
6 Oz kielbasa sausage, sliced
3 strips bacon, diced 
1 (16 Oz)can baked beans
1 can sweet corn
1 can diced tomatoes with green chilies
1/2 yellow onion, diced 
3 garlic cloves, diced
2 small russet potatoes, small diced
2 cups beef stock 
1 tbl onion powder
1 tbl garlic powder
2 tsp chili powder
Salt & Pepper tt 

Once all ingredients are combined, allow stew to simmer and reduce. Serve with crackers and enjoy 😋👩🏾‍🍳

Cajun Chicken & Shrimp Stuffed Shells 👩🏾‍🍳🤤

✨Recipe✨

2 chicken breast, cooked and chopped
1 box jumbo shells, cooked
1/2 small red onion, diced
2 tbl minced garlic
1/2 cup minced sundried tomatoes
2 cups shrimp, chopped
2 tbl italian seasonings
2 tbl cajun seasonings
1 tbl kosher salt
4 ounces ricotta cheese
4 ounces garlic and herb cream cheese
4 cups mozzarella cheese
1 jar Alfredo sauce

Thoroughly season your chicken breasts with Italian seasonings and kosher salt. Cook, chop and set aside. Sauté onion, garlic, tomato and add chopped shrimp. Set aside to cool and boil pasta. 

Combine cooked chicken and shrimp mixture. Stuff into jumbo shells and top with sauce, cheese and any remaining stuffing. Bake coved at 350 for 30 mins, then broil uncovered for 5. Serve and enjoy! 👩🏾‍🍳

🎄 Save this recipe for Christmas morning🎄 

Croissant Breakfast Bake 🫐🍓 

1 cup mixed berries (fresh or frozen)
2 eggs
2/3 cup sugar
1 tsp vanilla 
4 Croissants 🥐 
4 ounces cream cheese
3/4 cup milk 
1/2 cup @eatsantenuts cinnamon sugar almonds
3-4 tbl powdered sugar 

This is seriously as simple as it looks and can be assembled the night before and refrigerated for the morning! Rip up for croissants and place in grease casserole dish. Top with cream cheese mixture and @eatsantenuts almonds and bake covered at 350 for 30 mins. Remove cover and bake an additional 15. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve. 👩🏾‍🍳🤤

Southern Fried Chicken Wings 🤤👩🏾‍🍳 

1 lb chicken wings
1 tablespoon Onion powder
1 tablespoon Garlic powder
1 tablespoon Paprika
2 tsp Slap ya mama seasoning
2 cups flour
1 tablespoon Kosher salt 

Fry oil

Season chicken wings thoroughly with garlic, onion, paprika and slap ya mama. Set aside and heat oil. Add additional SYM seasoning to flour. Add flour to chicken half a cup at a time, tossing to drench each piece evenly in flour. Fry on all sides until golden brown. Finish in oven at 400 for desired crisp. I did about 5 mins on each side. Garnish with parsley and serve with ranch! Enjoy 👩🏾‍🍳

✨Crack Chicken Baked Potato✨

4 medium sized Baked Potatoes
2 Chicken breasts, grilled and sliced 
4 cups Broccoli, cooked and chopped 
5 sliced bacon, cooked and crumbled
2 cups cheddar cheese, shredded
1/2 cup ranch dressing 
1/2 cup Butter
2 tbls Ranch seasoning
Salt & Pepper tt 

Bakepotatoes until cooked throughly. Cut and gut potatoes, adding mashed potato to bowl and set aside. Salt and pepper empty potato skins. 

Add cooked broccoli, chicken, ranch, butter, ranch seasoning and cheese to potato mixture. Season with salt and pepper and mix thoroughly. Spoon mixture evenly into potato skins and top with additional cheese. Bake at 350 for 10 mins. Garnish with bacon crumble and serve. 👩🏾‍🍳

✨Bourbon Pecan Crusted Pork Loin✨

Y’all gotta make this one! So good and perfect for family dinner! 🍴🤤

Recipe:

1.5 lb boneless pork loin
2-3 tablespoons Dijon mustard
1 cup chopped @eatsantenuts bourbon pecans
1 tablespoon chopped fresh thyme
¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper 
1 tablespoon kosher Salt
1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper 

Bast pork loin in Dijon mustard. Set aside. Combine chopped pecans, thyme, cayenne, salt and pepper and mix well. Roll pork loin in nut mixture and place on greased sheet pan. Spray pork loin with cooking spray and bake at 350 for 25-30 or until internal temp of 145. Slice and enjoy! 👩🏾‍🍳

✨MILLION DOLLAR SPAGHETTI✨

16 ounces cooked spaghetti
1 pound ground beef
3-4 cloves garlic minced
1 medium onion diced (or ½ cup)
2 24-ounce jars spaghetti sauce
8 ounce ricotta cheese
1 egg
¼ cup sour cream
3 cups shredded mozzarella cheese 
1 tablespoon Italian seasoning 

Sweat onions and add garlic. Add ground beef and cook thoroughly. Add one jar of sauce and cooked spaghetti and set aside. Mix ricotta, one cup mozzarella, sour cream, egg, and Italian seasonings. Grease casserole dish and begin layering starting with half spaghetti meat sauce mixture and then ricotta mixture. Finish with last of spaghetti mixture and then top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes and then broil on low for 5 for a crispy cheese crust. Let rest for 10 mins and then serve! Enjoy! 👩🏾‍🍳

Roasted Carrots with @eatsantenuts Chipotle Almonds & Goat Cheese 🥕

✨ Recipe: ✨

Oven roasting carrots, 2-3 per person, peeled
1/2 cup brown sugar
4 tablespoons butter
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
4 ounces goat cheese crumbled
1/2 cup roughly chopped @eatsantenuts chipotle almonds 

Toss peeled carrots in butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt. Place a baking sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 60 minutes, turning 2-3 times to roast evenly. 

Plate and garnish with chopped @eatsantenuts Chipotle almonds and crumbled goat cheese. Serve and enjoy 👩🏾‍🍳😋

Heaven is a fresh baked Oreo Brownie🍫❤️

1 1/4 cups salted butter
2 1/2 cups light brown sugar
4 large eggs, room temperature
1 1/2 cups cocoa powder
3/4 teaspoon salt
2 teaspoons vanilla extract
2/3 cup all-purpose flour
16 Oreo cookies, crumbled into pieces

Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla extract. Add in cocoa powder, salt and flour. Fold in Oreo pieces, leaving about a handful to the side for the top. Add to greased baking dish and bake at 350 for 20 minutes. Pull brownies out and add remaining crumbled Oreos to top. Return to oven for additional 10 mins. Remove from oven and use butter knife to make sure brownies are cooked through! Enjoy! 👩🏾‍🍳🍫

#freshbaked #oreobrownies #oreo #bakingathome #whatsfordessert #foodiesofinstagram

✨Sweet & Spicy Pecan Crusted Chicken with @eatsantenuts ✨

The recipe:
2 Chicken breast
1 tsp onion powder
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tbl Salt
2 eggs
1 cup flour
2 cups chopped @eatsantenuts sweet and spicy pecans

Season chicken breast. Dip chicken in egg wash, then flour then back into egg wash, then into crumbled nuts. Spray coated chicken breast with pan spray and bake at 350 for 20 mins. Slice and serve! 👩🏾‍🍳😋

Happy 6 months to #MealPrepDelicious 👩🏾‍🍳❤️

Eating intentionally > Dieting 

As a society we are so used to eating out and going through the drive thru that when we make the choice to eat at home or meal prep there’s an assumption that we are dieting. 🤔 

One of my goals with #MealPrepDelicious is to break that stigma, and to help people see that eating intentionally is more life changing then any fad diet you can try. Intentional eating incorporates planning out your meals, making sure there’s variety of fruits, vegetables and proteins and most importantly, not wasting money or skipping meals. 😋 #foodforthought 

Whether you meal prep with me or own your own, do so knowing that what you feed your body, feeds you. 👩🏾‍🍳❤️
